WEBVTT

00:00.701 --> 00:05.037
             [♪♪♪]

00:41.408 --> 00:42.407
                  [SCREAMS]

00:42.409 --> 00:43.908
Aagh! What are you--?

00:43.910 --> 00:45.511
              Oh, master,
       what has happened to you?

00:45.513 --> 00:46.711
Huh? What do you mean?

00:46.713 --> 00:48.380
       You've turned green.

00:48.382 --> 00:51.082
 Oh. Heh, Jeannie,
  it's all right.

00:51.084 --> 00:52.784
It's my skin diving outfit.

00:52.786 --> 00:54.719
                       Oh.
         What?

00:54.721 --> 00:56.154
                 Thank heaven.

00:56.156 --> 00:57.722
         I thought that while
           I was sleeping,

00:57.724 --> 00:59.257
 someone had turned
   you into that.

00:59.259 --> 01:00.625
              [CHUCKLES]
                 No.

01:00.627 --> 01:03.628
Oh, where are you going, master?
It is 4:00 in the morning.

01:03.630 --> 01:06.131
    Uh, well, it's gonna be dawn
       in a couple of minutes.

01:06.133 --> 01:07.732
I'm going down to the beach.

01:07.734 --> 01:09.534
              Dressed like that?

01:09.536 --> 01:12.704
 Oh, Roger and I are going
hunting for sunken treasure.

01:12.706 --> 01:15.707
    Oh, that is a waste of time,
               master.

01:15.709 --> 01:18.243
I can give you all the treasures
          you desire.

01:18.245 --> 01:21.947
Uh, no, if you don't mind,
I'd rather find it myself.

01:21.949 --> 01:24.182
             If I live to be
         another 2000 years old,

01:24.184 --> 01:25.951
      I will not understand you.

01:25.953 --> 01:28.353
Well, it's not the treasure
I'm interested in, Jeannie.

01:28.355 --> 01:29.520
It's the hunt, you see.

01:31.424 --> 01:34.659
    How do you know
there is treasure there?

01:34.661 --> 01:36.761
            Well, I-I don't know
                  exactly.

01:36.763 --> 01:38.763
            It's just that, uh,
           a lot of pirate ships

01:38.765 --> 01:40.631
          used to ply the waters
            off the coast here,

01:40.633 --> 01:43.101
          and it's rumored
    that Captain Kidd had a ship

01:43.103 --> 01:45.270
         to go down with a lot
       of sunken treasure on it.

01:45.272 --> 01:47.705
  Who--? Who was
this Captain Kidd?

01:47.707 --> 01:50.441
             Oh, I was just
        reading about him. Here.

01:50.443 --> 01:52.244
             Now, let's see.
        Captain Kidd, Captain...

01:52.246 --> 01:53.478
          [MUMBLES INDISTINCTLY]

01:53.480 --> 01:55.313
                Oh, yeah.
            Uh, "William Kidd

01:55.315 --> 01:57.249
              "started out
        as a respectable seaman.

01:57.251 --> 01:58.850
         "The British government
               sent him out

01:58.852 --> 02:00.785
     "to harass the French fleet
               in 1700.

02:00.787 --> 02:02.420
            "His men forced him
             to turn renegade,

02:02.422 --> 02:04.622
      and he became a pirate."
    Well, he was quite a fellow.

02:04.624 --> 02:06.925
  It took the whole British navy
         to look for him.

02:06.927 --> 02:09.727
        [SCOFFS]
  I am sure he was not
as brave as you, master.

02:09.729 --> 02:11.229
                [CHUCKLES]
             Oh, no, Jeannie.

02:11.231 --> 02:13.498
      I'd hate to have tangled
   with him. I'll tell you that.

02:13.500 --> 02:15.967
Ah, I am sure you would have
    beaten him, master.

02:15.969 --> 02:17.068
              Oh, I doubt it.

02:17.070 --> 02:19.037
Oh, yes, you would have.

02:20.340 --> 02:21.739
That all right with you,
fellas?

02:21.741 --> 02:22.774
            [CHEERS]

02:22.776 --> 02:24.843
KIDD:
Hey, you!
               Huh?

02:24.845 --> 02:26.311
              Oh, who--? Me? Me?

02:26.313 --> 02:27.679
Yeah, you!

02:27.681 --> 02:29.381
    Kill him, Captain Kidd.

02:29.383 --> 02:31.883
With pleasure.
Prepare to die!

02:31.885 --> 02:33.918
              Uh, now, now, now,
                wait a minute!

02:33.920 --> 02:36.722
           Agh! Jeannie!
              Jeannie!

02:39.693 --> 02:41.727
             [♪♪♪]

03:28.709 --> 03:30.909
             [♪♪♪]

03:36.049 --> 03:39.050
                      Jeannie!
                      Jeannie!
[SHOUTING]

03:39.052 --> 03:41.353
  What was keeping you
     so long, huh?

03:41.355 --> 03:42.387
      I want--

03:42.389 --> 03:44.255
             Get him, master!

03:44.257 --> 03:46.191
    I don't know how to handle--

03:46.193 --> 03:48.159
             [♪♪♪]

03:52.265 --> 03:53.298
    I told you--

03:56.836 --> 03:58.336
                     [LAUGHING]

03:58.338 --> 04:00.071
Uh, I'm sorry, captain.

04:03.510 --> 04:05.510
  Wait! Will you wait?

04:10.216 --> 04:11.416
           [CHEERING]

04:27.000 --> 04:28.566
Kill him, master!

04:30.804 --> 04:32.104
                    Haaugh!

04:32.106 --> 04:33.238
         Aagh!

04:33.240 --> 04:35.440
        [WATER SPLASHES]

04:35.442 --> 04:37.376
             [♪♪♪]

04:44.851 --> 04:47.419
      He beat Captain Kidd.

04:47.421 --> 04:48.953
 [GIGGLES]

04:50.957 --> 04:52.323
   Any orders, captain?

04:52.325 --> 04:54.492
                           ALL:
                         Hooray!

04:54.494 --> 04:55.560
                Um, "captain"?

04:55.562 --> 04:57.362
       You'll be Captain Kidd.

04:57.364 --> 04:58.964
       You're our new leader.

04:58.966 --> 05:00.999
                     [ALL CHEER]

05:01.001 --> 05:02.901
    Well, I certainly appreciate
             your offer,

05:02.903 --> 05:05.169
          but I'm afraid
  I'm not gonna be able to stay.

05:05.171 --> 05:07.672
   You ain't thinkin' of runni''
        out on us, are you?

05:07.674 --> 05:09.440
       No. No, but I-I do have--

05:09.442 --> 05:12.477
    'Cause the only way anyone
     ever leaves this crew...

05:12.479 --> 05:14.479
         is feet first.

05:14.481 --> 05:15.980
                            ALL:
                           Yeah.

05:15.982 --> 05:17.115
                Feet first?

05:17.117 --> 05:18.917
                     Any orders?

05:18.919 --> 05:21.386
  Uh, no, no, not at the moment,
          but if I, um--

05:21.388 --> 05:23.588
           If I have any,
    I'll certainly let you know.

05:23.590 --> 05:24.756
        Aye, aye, captain.

05:24.758 --> 05:27.091
                   Back to work,
                    you lubbers.

05:27.093 --> 05:28.192
                You.

05:28.194 --> 05:29.294
        Me, sir?

05:29.296 --> 05:31.329
                   Yes.
          I wanna see you alone.

05:31.331 --> 05:34.533
Oh. Well, I-I have a lot of work
to do, captain, master.

05:34.535 --> 05:36.367
              No, no, no,
             I wanna talk--

05:37.971 --> 05:40.405
          What do you want to do
            with the prisoner?

05:40.407 --> 05:42.006
    Uh, prisoner?
What prisoner is that?

05:42.008 --> 05:44.309
          The girl we captured
       from the British frigate.

05:44.311 --> 05:46.311
  Oh, yes, yes.
  That prisoner.

05:46.313 --> 05:49.213
     Do you want to kill her,
      or do you want me to?

05:49.215 --> 05:50.448
      Kill her?
               I'll do it.

05:50.450 --> 05:51.582
                [LAUGHING]

05:51.584 --> 05:54.485
No, no, I'll do it.
    I'll do it.

05:54.487 --> 05:55.854
                Have fun.

05:55.856 --> 05:57.789
             [♪♪♪]

06:05.198 --> 06:06.631
              Boy.

06:09.202 --> 06:10.735
Hey.

06:10.737 --> 06:12.704
Hey, that's my cabin.

06:12.706 --> 06:14.906
     Yes, well, you're certainly
         a messy housekeeper.

06:14.908 --> 06:17.108
            Clean that place up.

06:17.110 --> 06:20.478
No, no, no.
She's in the captain's cabin.

06:20.480 --> 06:22.213
              All right.

06:25.485 --> 06:27.819
                  I'll call you
                when I need you.
   Oh, but--

06:29.690 --> 06:31.255
                 Don't touch me!
[STAMMERS]

06:31.257 --> 06:32.957
There's nothing
to worry about, ma'am.

06:32.959 --> 06:35.160
I'm Major Anthony Nelson,
United Stated Air Force.

06:35.162 --> 06:36.227
                    [SCREAMS]

06:36.229 --> 06:39.263
Shhh. I just wanna
cut your rope.

06:39.265 --> 06:40.732
Did you call me, captain?

06:40.734 --> 06:41.933
              Uh, no, I did not.

06:41.935 --> 06:43.735
           If I want you,
    I'll certainly let you know.

06:43.737 --> 06:46.137
               Now, go upstairs
             and swab the decks.

06:46.139 --> 06:47.939
Aye, captain.

06:49.475 --> 06:50.909
[DOOR CLOSES]

06:50.911 --> 06:52.811
   How did you get
on this ship, anyway?

06:52.813 --> 06:54.779
         As if you didn't know.

06:54.781 --> 06:56.147
           What did you do
           with the others?

06:56.149 --> 06:57.381
 Wh-what others?

06:57.383 --> 06:59.584
         Don't pretend you
    and your blood-thirsty crew

06:59.586 --> 07:01.385
            didn't board
     the <i> Yarmouth</i> and sink it.

07:01.387 --> 07:03.121
          But you'll pay for it.

07:03.123 --> 07:05.857
   Right now, there's a British
    frigate searching for you.

07:05.859 --> 07:07.725
  I didn't have anything to do
        with this, miss.

07:07.727 --> 07:09.260
Actually, I'm just passing by.

07:09.262 --> 07:10.828
      I'm gonna help you
      escape from here.

07:12.331 --> 07:13.464
    Do you really mean that?

07:13.466 --> 07:15.700
           Yes.
I told you if I need you--

07:15.702 --> 07:16.768
     Master?
              Oh.

07:16.770 --> 07:18.536
I think we'd better
leave here quickly.

07:18.538 --> 07:21.439
      We can't leave now.
They're going to kill this girl.

07:21.441 --> 07:23.441
        But if you stay,
  they are going to kill you.

07:23.443 --> 07:25.109
I heard them talking up on deck.

07:25.111 --> 07:27.044
      The first mate wants
     to take over the ship.

07:27.046 --> 07:29.581
  He can have it. But I'm not
 gonna leave here without her.

07:29.583 --> 07:31.516
     Very well, master.

07:31.518 --> 07:34.452
    I will try to find out
  how they plan to kill you.

07:34.454 --> 07:37.154
 Oh, you were right, master.
     This is so exciting!

07:37.156 --> 07:38.222
           [SQUEALS]

07:38.224 --> 07:40.258
           [CHUCKLES]

07:40.260 --> 07:41.593
           Who was that?

07:41.595 --> 07:44.929
        Oh, uh, that was
  an old, old friend of mine.

07:44.931 --> 07:47.064
  My husband will pay you well
     if you could save me.

07:47.066 --> 07:48.566
    He'll give you anything.

07:48.568 --> 07:50.301
  Oh, that's not necessary.

07:50.303 --> 07:52.604
           Forgive me.
   I haven't introduced myself.

07:52.606 --> 07:54.105
     I'm Lady Diane Nelson.

07:54.107 --> 07:57.408
    Oh, I'm, uh,
Major Anthony Nelson.

07:57.410 --> 08:00.612
 Did you say, uh,
Lady Diane Nelson?

08:00.614 --> 08:01.812
              Yes.

08:01.814 --> 08:04.949
Are you married to Lord Charles
         Alfred Nelson?

08:04.951 --> 08:06.151
     You know my husband?

08:06.153 --> 08:08.553
          Know him?
             Why,

08:08.555 --> 08:12.190
   he's my great-great-great-
       great-grandfather.

08:12.192 --> 08:13.658
       I beg your pardon.

08:13.660 --> 08:14.960
  And that means that you're

08:14.962 --> 08:17.028
    my great-great-great-
      great-grandmother.

08:17.030 --> 08:18.463
   What are you talking about?

08:18.465 --> 08:22.033
You're gonna have a son named--
   Named, uh-- Named William,

08:22.035 --> 08:24.235
     and you're gonna have
  a daughter named Priscilla.

08:24.237 --> 08:25.837
That is, if I can get you
     off this boat.

08:25.839 --> 08:28.206
And if I can't get you off this
  boat, I'm not gonna be born.

08:28.208 --> 08:29.407
                    [SCREAMING]
            Shhh.

08:29.409 --> 08:30.908
        Oh, please,
       don't do that.

08:30.910 --> 08:33.111
                [SCREAMING]

08:33.113 --> 08:34.412
     Captain?

08:34.414 --> 08:35.679
              Oh, what are you
                doing here?

08:35.682 --> 08:36.982
What's taking you so long?

08:36.984 --> 08:38.850
             We can't kill her.
       What?

08:38.852 --> 08:41.019
          I mean-- I mean,
       we can't kill her now.

08:41.020 --> 08:42.919
               Look, uh...
                 I, uh--

08:42.922 --> 08:44.756
   I think we should torture her
           a little bit.

08:44.758 --> 08:46.824
       She's probably got plenty
           of hidden treasure

08:46.826 --> 08:48.192
      she could tell us about.

08:48.194 --> 08:50.528
Ohhh, good thinking.

08:50.530 --> 08:51.796
          [BOTH LAUGH]

08:51.798 --> 08:53.264
       Yeah, go boil some water.

08:53.266 --> 08:54.598
 Yeah-- Boil some water?

08:54.600 --> 08:56.734
              And-- And heat up
              a branding iron.

08:56.736 --> 08:59.737
All right, skipper.

08:59.739 --> 09:01.806
             Oh, no!
        No, you promised!

09:01.808 --> 09:04.441
                   [SOBBING]
               No, you promised!
                 You promised!

09:04.443 --> 09:06.744
No, I'm not gonna let anybody
          hurt you.

09:06.746 --> 09:10.281
I was just using that to stall
        for some time.

09:10.283 --> 09:12.784
    But how are you gonna get me
            off the ship?

09:12.786 --> 09:15.252
       Uh, I've got
a very influential friend.

09:15.254 --> 09:16.688
Now, you just stay right there.

09:16.690 --> 09:18.322
  Uh, don't go away.
       Be calm.

09:18.324 --> 09:19.824
             [♪♪♪]

09:19.826 --> 09:20.892
          Don't go away.

09:23.997 --> 09:25.629
  Jeannie, where have you been?

09:25.631 --> 09:27.799
       Give me that thing.
 You're gonna cut your head off.

09:27.801 --> 09:29.167
Are you ready to leave,
        master?

09:29.169 --> 09:30.334
           I-I can't leave yet.

09:30.336 --> 09:31.936
               Do you know who
                that girl is?
       No.

09:31.938 --> 09:34.672
  That's my great-great-great-
       great-grandmother.

09:34.674 --> 09:35.740
            Really?

09:37.043 --> 09:38.943
Well, I never would've known it.

09:38.945 --> 09:40.544
   She does not look a bit
          like you.

09:40.546 --> 09:42.646
 That's not the point, Jeannie.

09:42.648 --> 09:44.715
The point is, if I don't get her
         off this ship,

09:44.717 --> 09:46.217
           there's not
         gonna be any me.

09:46.219 --> 09:48.686
How are you going to rescue her,
       master? You are in

09:48.688 --> 09:50.221
as much danger as she is.
            Shh-shh.

09:50.223 --> 09:51.522
   You should--

09:51.524 --> 09:54.292
  You should hear
their plans for you.

09:54.294 --> 09:57.294
I'm gonna sneak her off the ship
  and get her on that island.

09:57.296 --> 09:59.897
 She told me there's a British
frigate looking for the pirates.

09:59.899 --> 10:01.599
      I'll find out some way
        of signaling 'em.

10:01.601 --> 10:03.500
Oh, that is a wonderful idea--

10:03.502 --> 10:05.236
            Hey you!
         Back to work.

10:05.238 --> 10:06.738
   Yeah, yeah, get back to work.

10:06.740 --> 10:08.039
       Aye, aye, sir.

10:11.144 --> 10:13.510
 The iron will be hot
     in a minute.

10:13.512 --> 10:15.579
  When it's through,
  I just can't wait

10:15.581 --> 10:18.116
to see her walk the plank.

10:18.118 --> 10:19.283
                Yeah, yeah.

10:19.285 --> 10:21.052
              [CHUCKLES]
      It'll be a billion laughs.

10:21.054 --> 10:22.586
             [♪♪♪]

10:26.459 --> 10:28.692
I don't trust that one.

10:28.694 --> 10:31.362
  He has an honest face.

10:31.364 --> 10:33.397
       Get the men
 and let's take him now.

10:33.399 --> 10:35.133
               Aye, aye, mate.

10:46.146 --> 10:47.879
                  [GASPS]
         Shh-shh.

10:47.881 --> 10:50.048
I have a plan. I'm gonna
 get you off this boat.

10:50.050 --> 10:51.148
                   Oh, how?

10:51.150 --> 10:52.249
           Heh?
                     How?

10:52.251 --> 10:54.018
    Oh, uh, I want you
 to put on these clothes.

10:54.020 --> 10:56.187
 We'll sneak you off this ship
    and over to the island.

10:56.189 --> 10:58.089
      That British frigate
     you were talking about

10:58.091 --> 10:59.457
        should be along
        any minute now.

10:59.459 --> 11:01.026
And we'll send up smoke signals.

11:01.028 --> 11:02.961
Master? Master?

11:02.963 --> 11:04.996
      Oh, hurry, they are coming
              after you.
  Why?

11:04.998 --> 11:06.531
                   To kill you.

11:06.533 --> 11:08.499
Oh, Jeannie, they can't do that.

11:08.501 --> 11:11.602
    I'm-- I'm the captain
        of this boat.

11:11.604 --> 11:13.071
         [BOTH SCREAM]

11:13.073 --> 11:14.138
What do we do now?

11:14.140 --> 11:16.174
 We're gonna change our plans.

11:16.176 --> 11:17.342
        [SWORD SLASHES]
            Naagh!

11:20.880 --> 11:22.513
      There they are. Get 'em!

11:22.515 --> 11:25.516
          All right, stand back.
          Stand back! I mean it!

11:25.518 --> 11:28.118
  All right, you asked for it.

11:29.689 --> 11:30.922
           Go up the back steps.

11:30.924 --> 11:33.157
    There are no back steps!

11:33.159 --> 11:35.326
          They don't build ships
           the way they used to.

11:38.431 --> 11:39.530
                Grab him!

11:39.532 --> 11:40.665
Aye, aye, captain.

11:40.667 --> 11:42.533
         No! No!
   Wait a minute, wait a minute.

11:42.535 --> 11:45.503
   Take your hands off of me.
I don't think you know who I am.

11:45.505 --> 11:47.672
    I happen to be
Major Anthony Nelson,

11:47.674 --> 11:51.209
  in the Air Force
of the United States.

11:51.211 --> 11:53.678
      And if you're wise,
you'll let me walk out of here.

11:53.680 --> 11:57.048
 Oh, you want to take a walk,
           do ya?

11:57.050 --> 11:58.549
All right.

11:59.386 --> 12:01.719
      Tomorrow at sunrise,

12:01.721 --> 12:03.821
     you'll walk the plank.

12:03.823 --> 12:05.156
[CACKLING]

12:05.158 --> 12:06.290
Take 'em to the brig.

12:06.292 --> 12:07.691
           Now, wait a minute.
          [SCREAMS]

12:07.693 --> 12:09.494
Take your hands off--
       Oh, oh.

12:09.496 --> 12:11.295
             [♪♪♪]

12:17.003 --> 12:18.903
          Pull 'em up!

12:18.905 --> 12:20.471
      Hey, wait a minute.

12:20.473 --> 12:22.907
Which one of you wants
to walk the plank first?

12:22.909 --> 12:23.941
                       Wait!

12:23.943 --> 12:25.542
    Let him walk the plank.

12:25.544 --> 12:27.044
                  But the girl--

12:27.046 --> 12:29.513
  You save the girl for us, huh!

12:29.515 --> 12:30.748
                      [GASPS]
              ALL:
          Yeah, yeah.

12:30.750 --> 12:32.016
No, no, no.

12:32.018 --> 12:33.851
They both got to walk the plank.

12:33.853 --> 12:36.520
  We don't want any witnesses.

12:36.522 --> 12:38.656
      Here!
Smell that smoke.

12:38.658 --> 12:40.524
    Ah-ha-ha.

12:40.526 --> 12:43.161
Oh-ho-ho. Yes.

12:43.163 --> 12:44.762
  Eh. Wait a second.

12:44.764 --> 12:46.865
Ladies, first.

12:46.867 --> 12:48.466
[LAUGHS]
        [GASPING]

12:49.702 --> 12:52.436
[LAUGHS]
Give my regards
to Captain Kidd,

12:52.438 --> 12:54.505
will ya, now?

12:54.507 --> 12:56.274
   This isn't legal, you know.
         You can get in

12:56.276 --> 12:58.076
   a lot of trouble for this.
Really, where?

12:58.078 --> 13:00.578
Don't keep the sharks
waitin' now, will you?

13:00.580 --> 13:02.213
         [CANNON BOOMS]

13:02.215 --> 13:05.116
          Hey, there's a British
         man-of-war approaching!

13:08.154 --> 13:09.520
             [♪♪♪]

13:10.723 --> 13:13.658
               Oh. It's headin'
                  this way.

13:13.660 --> 13:15.059
         [CANNON BOOMS]

13:20.233 --> 13:22.933
   What are we gonna do?
     They will sink us.

13:22.935 --> 13:25.169
              No, they won't.

13:25.171 --> 13:28.473
          Not as long as we hold
           Lady Diane prisoner.

13:28.475 --> 13:29.640
                  [LAUGHS]

13:31.344 --> 13:32.443
                  [GRUNTING]

13:32.445 --> 13:33.611
           They're gettin' away!

13:34.681 --> 13:36.581
Ah, get 'em! Get 'em!

13:36.583 --> 13:38.950
                   [GRUNTING]

13:38.952 --> 13:40.952
                  Ah, get 'em!
                    Get 'em!

13:40.954 --> 13:43.320
           They're gettin' away.

13:43.322 --> 13:44.755
Get 'em! Get 'em! Get 'em!

13:51.697 --> 13:54.232
   They're gonna catch us!

13:58.638 --> 14:00.471
             [♪♪♪]

14:12.185 --> 14:13.217
        [BOAT SCREECHES]

14:16.656 --> 14:17.788
                  What now?

14:17.790 --> 14:19.190
There's nothing
to worry about.

14:19.192 --> 14:20.992
We'll hide here
until the British arrive.

14:20.994 --> 14:22.493
        Master, may I help you?

14:22.495 --> 14:24.162
 No, certainly not.

14:24.164 --> 14:25.463
           Well, then I am going
                 to leave.

14:25.465 --> 14:26.965
       Why?

14:26.967 --> 14:30.234
  Because I do not want to stay
 and watch them bury you at sea.

14:30.236 --> 14:31.635
                    [WHIMPERING]

14:31.637 --> 14:34.205
           [WEEPING]

14:34.207 --> 14:36.073
Now-- Now, look what you've--

14:36.075 --> 14:38.509
  Now, you see
what you've done?

14:38.511 --> 14:41.045
TONY:
Now, you see what you did?
Will you please relax?

14:41.047 --> 14:42.546
      Now, believe me,
     I have everything

14:42.548 --> 14:44.849
  completely under control.

14:45.651 --> 14:47.652
        [LADY DIANE SHRIEKS]

14:47.654 --> 14:49.287
        [BOTH SCREAMING]

14:54.327 --> 14:55.326
                [BOTH SCREAMING]

14:55.328 --> 14:57.395
             [♪♪♪]

15:00.566 --> 15:02.233
                   Agh!

15:02.235 --> 15:04.434
[INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

15:04.436 --> 15:07.171
Uh, you two go on ahead.
I'll try to hold 'em off.

15:07.173 --> 15:08.673
      [SCREAMING]

15:08.675 --> 15:10.475
           [SCREAMS]

15:14.447 --> 15:15.779
         Oh.

15:15.781 --> 15:17.415
Thanks. Thanks a lot.

15:17.417 --> 15:20.118
     You are the bravest master
            I've ever had.

15:20.120 --> 15:22.219
           Come on, mateys.

15:22.221 --> 15:25.489
Thank you. Oh, Jeannie,
you get going, will ya?

15:25.491 --> 15:27.191
They're coming.
    Go on.
                  [SCREAMS]

15:28.961 --> 15:30.161
 Jeannie, what is this?

15:32.532 --> 15:34.132
         Jeannie!
      What is this?!

15:34.134 --> 15:35.400
           [GUNSHOT]

15:38.404 --> 15:40.304
           [GUNSHOTS]

15:43.943 --> 15:45.776
           [GUNSHOT]

15:57.890 --> 15:58.923
            [BONKS]

15:58.925 --> 16:00.791
           [GUNSHOTS]

16:12.672 --> 16:14.472
           [BONKING]

16:17.343 --> 16:18.676
     [INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

16:19.845 --> 16:21.812
           [GUNSHOTS]

16:33.860 --> 16:34.892
            Agh!

16:34.894 --> 16:36.794
                 Master.
         Let us get out of here.

16:36.796 --> 16:39.130
 Yeah, we're not gonna be able
   to hold out much longer.

16:39.132 --> 16:40.597
             Agh!

16:40.599 --> 16:42.699
          Lady Diane,
  would you excuse me, please?

16:43.903 --> 16:45.569
    [SCREAMS]

16:47.706 --> 16:48.839
             What are you doing?

16:48.841 --> 16:50.174
I have a plan, Jeannie.

16:50.176 --> 16:52.542
I'm gonna make a white flag.
  If I can give myself up,

16:52.544 --> 16:54.912
maybe they'll let you
 and Lady Diane go.

16:54.914 --> 16:57.381
LADY DIANE:
I won't let them
capture me again.

16:58.550 --> 17:00.084
           [GUNSHOTS]

17:03.055 --> 17:04.789
         What is your next plan,
                 master?

17:04.790 --> 17:06.790
           [GUNSHOT]

17:06.792 --> 17:08.693
    It's no use.
 They're closing in.

17:08.694 --> 17:10.361
Jeannie, we gotta get her
      out of here.

17:10.363 --> 17:13.030
       I know. If they kill her,
        there will not be a you.

17:13.031 --> 17:15.266
     Yeah.
               And I would not
            like that very much.

17:15.268 --> 17:16.834
Yeah, neither would I.

17:16.836 --> 17:18.736
           [GUNSHOTS]

17:18.738 --> 17:20.003
          I know what I will do.

17:22.308 --> 17:23.573
             [♪♪♪]

17:23.575 --> 17:25.510
                 Attention!

17:27.946 --> 17:29.380
The Marines have landed.

17:29.382 --> 17:31.415
       Oh, they are not Marines,
                master.

17:31.417 --> 17:33.350
       They are British soldiers
           from the frigate.

17:33.352 --> 17:36.053
That's just a figure of speech,
           Jeannie.

17:36.055 --> 17:38.856
I'll never say an unkind word
      about you again.

17:38.858 --> 17:40.257
                     Aww.
        Hey!

17:40.259 --> 17:41.725
                     Take aim.
              TONY: Here we are!

17:41.727 --> 17:43.160
                        Fire!

17:45.798 --> 17:47.198
Can't you do anything right?

17:47.200 --> 17:48.932
           I am sorry, master.

17:48.934 --> 17:50.401
Now we're really in a trap.

17:50.403 --> 17:52.403
If the pirates don't shoot us,
      the British will.

17:52.405 --> 17:53.737
           [GUNSHOTS]

17:55.007 --> 17:56.607
      Hey! Hey, fellas!
 CAPTAIN: Ready.

17:56.609 --> 17:57.841
Take aim.
             Hey!

17:57.843 --> 17:58.842
                         Fire!

18:01.314 --> 18:03.614
                   Here.
          Try once more, master.

18:03.616 --> 18:05.416
Where's the flag?
Give me the flag.

18:05.418 --> 18:06.517
            JEANNIE:
          It is here.

18:06.519 --> 18:07.984
[GUNSHOTS]

18:12.858 --> 18:14.358
               Hold your fire!

18:14.360 --> 18:15.992
         That did it!

18:15.994 --> 18:18.195
Oh! We're saved.

18:18.197 --> 18:20.130
[WEEPING]

18:21.134 --> 18:23.467
Oh, Jeannie, I-I--
   I'm sorry--

18:23.469 --> 18:25.135
                I know, I know,
              you will never say

18:25.137 --> 18:26.871
             another unkind word
               about me again.

18:26.873 --> 18:28.839
    I only said it
in the heat of action.

18:28.841 --> 18:31.408
 Hey! Hey, there,
  here we come.

18:31.410 --> 18:33.578
     You know,
British flag. Ha-ha!

18:33.580 --> 18:36.714
          Hey! Hey!
       Hey, flag. See?

18:36.716 --> 18:38.082
         Hey! Ha-ha!

18:39.385 --> 18:41.218
[CHUCKLING]
Hey!

18:43.556 --> 18:45.222
        Lady Diane.
     Are you all right?

18:45.224 --> 18:47.458
              Oh, now I am.

18:47.460 --> 18:49.526
   Get the rest
 of those pirates.

18:49.528 --> 18:50.795
                     [CHUCKLING]
                         Hey!

18:50.797 --> 18:52.997
           Boy, are you a sight
              for sore eyes.

18:52.999 --> 18:54.732
      You got here just in time.

18:54.734 --> 18:56.266
    Splendid.
    Hang him.

18:56.268 --> 18:58.569
     Hang him? Wait a minute.
    I'm one of the good guys.

18:58.571 --> 19:00.972
               Captain, this man
                 saved my life.

19:00.974 --> 19:02.672
         It was nothing.
       Anybody would do it.

19:02.674 --> 19:05.109
We have orders to hang
all pirates on sight.

19:05.111 --> 19:06.877
           I happen to be
       Major Anthony Nelson,

19:06.879 --> 19:09.480
    United States Air Force,
  on detached service to NASA.

19:09.482 --> 19:11.248
                Is there no way
                 to save him?

19:11.250 --> 19:13.617
       None, ma'am.
We're under king's orders.

19:13.619 --> 19:15.752
Escort Lady Diane
  to the ship.

19:15.754 --> 19:17.087
        Now, wait a minute.
               Wait.

19:17.089 --> 19:18.122
LADY DIANE:
Goodbye.

19:18.124 --> 19:20.291
             I guess you're not
                going to be

19:20.293 --> 19:24.328
           my great-great-great-
              great-grandson.

19:24.330 --> 19:26.163
          I guess I'm not.

19:27.467 --> 19:28.666
                Here.

19:29.969 --> 19:32.036
CAPTAIN:
Continue the execution.

19:32.038 --> 19:33.270
                Jeannie!

19:34.107 --> 19:35.906
     [INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

19:37.309 --> 19:38.976
           [GUNSHOTS]

19:48.955 --> 19:49.954
  [MAGIC BOINGS]

19:52.558 --> 19:54.324
                      [GUNSHOTS]

20:03.202 --> 20:04.902
TONY:
Jeannie!
Jeannie!

20:04.904 --> 20:07.037
Wait a minute.
Jeannie!

20:07.039 --> 20:08.439
         Wait a minute,
       this is a mistake.

20:08.441 --> 20:10.074
  Wait a minute, you guys.

20:10.076 --> 20:12.409
           Jeannie!
           Jeannie!

20:12.411 --> 20:14.578
   Now, come on, I mean it.
         Just-- Just--

20:14.580 --> 20:15.746
        Wait a minute, you guys.

20:15.748 --> 20:18.482
                I'm not exactly
              who I-I, um, seem.

20:18.484 --> 20:19.850
                    Please.

20:19.852 --> 20:21.218
                Jeannie!

20:22.789 --> 20:24.555
                      Attention!

20:24.557 --> 20:26.290
                       Ready!

20:28.360 --> 20:29.860
        Wait a minute!

20:29.862 --> 20:31.461
               Go!

20:41.874 --> 20:43.106
     Knock that--

20:43.108 --> 20:45.742
       Oh, that was fun, master.
          Can we do it again?

20:45.744 --> 20:47.010
         No.

20:47.012 --> 20:50.381
Would you--? Would you please
     get me out of this?

20:50.383 --> 20:53.417
       I told you you would beat
         Captain Kidd, master.

20:53.419 --> 20:56.253
The next time I open my mouth,
        don't listen.

20:56.255 --> 20:58.722
     Oh, it was nothing, master.

20:58.724 --> 20:59.956
        [DOORBELL RINGS]

20:59.958 --> 21:01.091
        Oh.

21:01.794 --> 21:03.227
         [MAGIC BOINGS]

21:03.229 --> 21:04.395
  Yes, can I help you?

21:04.397 --> 21:06.497
              Got anything
       that needs killin', mate?

21:07.733 --> 21:08.965
  How--? How did you get here?

21:08.967 --> 21:10.401
            In my car.

21:10.403 --> 21:12.035
        In your car?

21:12.037 --> 21:14.772
     I'm from The Quick Kill
      Exterminating Service.

21:14.774 --> 21:17.274
         If you got 'em,
           we kill 'em.

21:17.276 --> 21:18.709
             [LAUGHS]

21:18.711 --> 21:20.844
         [CHUCKLES]
      Yeah. Oh, yeah.

21:20.846 --> 21:22.413
 It's-- It's-- It's remarkable.

21:22.415 --> 21:23.547
             That's right, mate.

21:23.549 --> 21:25.416
                And we guarantee
                  all our work.

21:25.418 --> 21:27.618
                Would you like
               a demonstration?

21:27.620 --> 21:28.919
          Oh no, th--

21:28.921 --> 21:30.521
     Thank you, I've had
      a very trying day.

21:30.523 --> 21:32.122
Perhaps some other time, yes?

21:32.124 --> 21:34.991
     Just as you say, mate.
         I'll be back.

21:34.993 --> 21:36.226
            Cheerio.

21:36.228 --> 21:38.162
    Cheerio.

21:38.164 --> 21:40.564
             [♪♪♪]

21:41.800 --> 21:42.933
       [LAUGHING]
                     Oh?

21:42.935 --> 21:44.468
              Did you see him?
              Did you see him?

21:44.470 --> 21:45.502
     Yes, master.

21:45.504 --> 21:47.003
          I-i-it was the pirate.
                It was him.

21:47.005 --> 21:49.940
I think it was his great-great-
  great-great-great-grandson.

21:49.942 --> 21:51.475
                  Huh? Oh.

21:51.477 --> 21:53.844
                 Oh, yes,
             of course it was.

21:53.846 --> 21:55.312
            But you know what?
         Hm?

21:55.314 --> 21:57.414
               He's still in
             the same business.

21:57.416 --> 21:59.283
             [♪♪♪]

22:02.288 --> 22:03.888
             [♪♪♪]

22:03.890 --> 22:05.489
              [GRUNTING]

22:09.462 --> 22:11.562
That was very good, master.

22:11.564 --> 22:14.465
         Oh, well, I was just
     practicing up my sword arm.

22:14.467 --> 22:16.400
         It's a little sore.
     I have to keep it in shape.

22:16.402 --> 22:17.435
       Oh.

22:17.437 --> 22:19.303
Did you enjoy being a pirate,
          master?

22:19.305 --> 22:21.672
  Well, I shouldn't admit it,
           but, uh...

22:21.674 --> 22:22.973
        Yeah, I loved it.

22:22.975 --> 22:24.608
      Oh, I am glad!

22:24.610 --> 22:27.110
  Are there any other pirates
you would like to meet, master?

22:27.112 --> 22:28.546
        Eh, no, no, no, no.

22:28.548 --> 22:30.280
          You've met one,
        you've met 'em all.

22:31.316 --> 22:32.850
        Oh, I...

22:32.852 --> 22:34.451
      I suppose so.

22:34.453 --> 22:37.187
I liked your great-great-great-
  great-grandmother, though.

22:37.189 --> 22:39.089
            Oh, yes.
 She was wonderful, wasn't she?

22:39.091 --> 22:40.090
            Mm.

22:40.092 --> 22:42.192
        I have a little trouble
            thinking of her

22:42.194 --> 22:44.127
    as a sweet little old lady.

22:44.129 --> 22:45.328
     She had a lot of courage.

22:45.330 --> 22:46.663
          Oh, yes.

22:46.665 --> 22:48.799
And your great-great-great-
     great-grandfather

22:48.801 --> 22:50.133
   was very brave also.

22:51.637 --> 22:52.903
      And handsome.

22:52.905 --> 22:54.571
  I wonder what he looked like?

22:54.573 --> 22:56.006
  Would you really
   like to know?

22:56.008 --> 22:57.407
                   Yes.

22:57.409 --> 22:59.309
  No, no, I don't wanna go back.
         Really, I don't.

22:59.311 --> 23:00.811
Oh, this will interest you,
          master.

23:00.813 --> 23:03.179
            No, Jeannie, please.
                 Yeah, uh--

23:03.181 --> 23:04.515
                     Oh.

23:04.517 --> 23:05.516
                   Say.

23:05.518 --> 23:07.951
<i> "The Book of English Nobility."</i>

23:07.953 --> 23:10.286
          How about that?
           Hm.

23:10.288 --> 23:11.321
          There's Lady Diane.

23:11.323 --> 23:13.757
                   JEANNIE:
              Oh, she is lovely.

23:13.759 --> 23:15.559
What did her husband look like?

23:18.330 --> 23:20.397
TONY [CHUCKLING]:
How 'bout that.

23:20.399 --> 23:21.398
        [LAUGHING]

23:21.400 --> 23:23.066
I wonder what would've happened

23:23.068 --> 23:24.735
    if we hadn't been able
         to save her.

23:24.737 --> 23:26.670
      I-I mean, if I'd had
      the same grandfather

23:26.672 --> 23:28.271
 but a different grandmother.

23:28.273 --> 23:30.907
Would you really like to know,
           master?

23:30.909 --> 23:32.476
             Yeah, yeah.

23:32.478 --> 23:33.711
    Would I look very different?

23:33.713 --> 23:35.078
     [GIGGLES]

23:35.080 --> 23:36.913
      A little.

23:36.915 --> 23:38.549
     [LAUGHING]

23:41.053 --> 23:43.053
           [IN BRITISH ACCENT]
         Now, see here, Jeannie.

23:43.055 --> 23:45.288
            I don't think this
             is funny at all.

23:45.290 --> 23:47.057
               You are being
          absolutely ridiculous.

23:47.059 --> 23:48.158
             Now, you stop this.

23:48.160 --> 23:49.960
             [♪♪♪]

23:51.364 --> 23:52.696
               It's a bit much.

23:57.302 --> 24:01.472
             [♪♪♪]
